        <p>Dear Palanivel, Muthuvel, and Saravanan,<br>
          <br>
          I have reviewed both documents from the QA mail ID — the IST-1
          to IST-7 questionnaire responses and the po_para column
          analysis. I want to acknowledge the effort made to complete
          these before  meeting, and then be precise about what still
          needs to be done before the FSD can proceed to CEO approval.<br>
          <br>
          <b>What is well done and confirmed</b><br>
          <br>
          <b>IST-1 is the most important answer in this entire
            submission.</b> Muthuvel confirms that the PR form is common
          to all clients with zero customer-specific customisations.
          This directly closes the CustID hardcoding question that has
          been open since the first review cycle. FSD Section 11 can now
          be formally updated to record: 'Zero customer-specific
          variations. PR form behaviour is fully parameter-driven.
          Confirmed by Module Sr IST.' This is a foundational
          confirmation for SPINRISE.<br>
          <br>
          <b>IST-2 provides the key SPINRISE architectural decision for
            the PR approval workflow.</b> The current system supports 3
          levels (1 in VB, 2 in Web), with Level 2 bypass being standard
          practice. Muthuvel recommends 2 levels for SPINRISE: Level 1
          by Department Heads, Level 2 by Purchase Officer. Management
          approval is not required for PRs. This is the answer the CEO
          has been waiting for. It is a clear and actionable
          recommendation. It also confirms a critical point: PO
          generation after approval is a SEPARATE MANUAL STEP — there is
          no auto-PO creation from an approved PR. SPINRISE must reflect
          this: the PR approval workflow ends with a Final Approved
          status, and PO creation is a separate user action.<br>
          <br>
          <b>IST-5 confirms that the PR form is not affected by
            financial year boundaries in the same way other modules are.</b>
          Once PP_Year is enabled for the new year, PR creation is
          available. No year-end complications specific to this form.<br>
          <br>
          <b>IST-6 provides an important new business rule. </b>Modification
          and deletion are allowed only when the PR is in OPEN status.
          Once the first level of approval is given, both Modify and
          Delete are disabled. This is a stricter guard than what the
          VB6 code currently enforces and must be implemented in
          SPINRISE. <b>Mariyaiya, please add this</b> to FSD Section 4
          under Delete Validations and to Section 5 under the Modify
          Guard: once PRSTATUS moves beyond OPEN (i.e., any approval
          flag is set), Modify and Delete must both be hard-blocked.<br>
          <br>
          <b>IST-7 provides an important scope clarification</b>. The PO
          module does not have a backdate parameter at all. The backdate
          configuration is in the Store Inventory module only. For
          SPINRISE, the decision is clear: no backdate for PR entry. PR
          date equals processing date only. This must be documented in
          FSD Section 12 as a confirmed SPINRISE design decision, not a
          pending item.<br>
          <br>
          The po_para column analysis correctly identifies 63 total
          columns, flags 10 as unused or legacy, and correctly
          identifies EmpMasterComm as an active column — which confirms
          the EmpCommon origin finding from Mariyaiya's earlier
          analysis. The identification of Trans_* log columns as archive
          fields is also correct.<br>
          <br>
          <br>
          <b>What needs to be corrected or completed</b><br>
          <br>
          Before this IST review can be treated as complete, the
          following items must be addressed.<br>
          <br>
          <b>1. IST-3 — SP behaviour answer is not from IST experience.</b><br>
          Muthuvel's response to IST-3 says 'developer confirmed no
          customer-specific variations.' The IST question asks for
          confirmation from field experience at customer sites, not a
          relay of what the developer said. Muthuvel, as IST, you have
          implemented and supported the PO module at many customer sites
          over the years. Have you personally observed any scenario
          where SP_GetStock returned wrong stock values, where
          KSP_INDEDNT_CHECK blocked a legitimate item, or where
          ksp_PendPR caused problems at a customer site? That is what
          this question is asking. Please provide your own confirmation
          based on your site experience, not the developer's.
          Additionally, the SP code for these three procedures has not
          been submitted to Claude via Follow-up Prompt B. This is
          mandatory per the v2 guide before Section 8 can be finalised.<br>
          <br>
          <b>2. IST-4 — support call patterns are too thin.</b><br>
          Two items is not sufficient. Muthuvel has handled PR form
          support calls across all Kalsofte customers for over the
          years. PM Saravanan's equivalent response for the RMI PO
          module gave 9 specific customer pain points covering GST rate
          mismatches, UoM/ArrivalType inconsistencies, navigation bugs,
          and tax calculation errors. <b>That is the standard.</b> For
          the PR form, please provide a more complete list of real
          support issues: what do users get wrong when raising a PR?
          What corrections does IST have to make at customer sites? What
          validation errors recur frequently? What data quality issues
          have occurred in pr_datt or po_prh that SPINRISE should
          prevent by design?<br>
          <br>
          <b>3. po_para document — three specific corrections needed.</b><br>
          First, the document date says April 2025. Please correct to
          April 2026 before submitting for approval.<br>
          <br>
          <b>Second, the SPINRISE default value is missing for every
            flag</b>. The CEO's request was for two things: (a) current
          usage status — which you have provided, and (b) recommended
          SPINRISE default for a new customer installation — which is
          absent. For the 6 flags that are relevant to the PR form
          (Manual_IndNo, BudgetQty, PRapprovalstatus, Penpodetails,
          PendingOrderPara, InditemGrp), please add a 'SPINRISE Default'
          column stating what value a new customer should have on their
          first SPINRISE installation. This is not the same as the
          current VB6 default.<br>
          <br>
          <b>Third, please clarify whether ManIndNo and Manual_IndNo are
            the same column with a spelling variation or two distinct
            columns.</b> Both appear in the table with different Status
          values. If they are the same column, one entry must be
          removed.<br>
          <br>
          <b>4. PR Approval workflow — three sub-questions still open.</b><br>
          IST-2 has confirmed the structure (2 levels recommended, L1 =
          Dept Heads, L2 = Purchase Officer). But three specific
          questions remain unanswered that block the SPINRISE workflow
          design:<br>
          (a) Which VB form or screen handles the actual approval
          action? Muthuvel mentions 1 level in VB but does not name the
          form.<br>
          (b) Which Web module handles the other 2 levels? URL or module
          name?<br>
          (c) Are the approval levels currently configurable per
          customer, or are all live customers on the same 3-level
          structure?<br>
          <br>
          <b>5. OCX UserFooter — still pending from Palanivel.</b><br>
          This question has been asked in two previous mail threads and
          is still unanswered. Palanivel: is the custom footer selection
          functionality (PurOrd.UserFooter OCX) actively used by
          customers when printing PRs, or is it a legacy feature that is
          rarely used in practice? A one-word answer (yes, it is used /
          no, it is not used) is all that is needed. This determines
          whether SPINRISE must implement a server-side footer selection
          dropdown.<br>
          <br>
          <br>
          <b>On Palanivel's TL-IST submission</b><br>
          <br>
          Palanivel, I note that your submission is effectively a
          forwarding of Muthuvel's work to PM Saravanan for approval.
          The TL-IST role in the review chain is to independently verify
          Muthuvel's answers, add any corrections or additions from your
          own senior IST experience, and then formally sign off. A
          forwarding mail without independent commentary is not a TL-IST
          sign-off. Please review Muthuvel's IST-1 to IST-7 responses
          and provide your own remarks — do you agree with each answer,
          do you have additional context, or do you disagree with any of
          Muthuvel's assessments? Particularly on IST-2 (approval
          levels) and IST-4 (support calls), your experience of working
          with spinning mill customers adds important context.<br>
          <br>
          <br>
          <b>For Mariyaiya — FSD update actions from this IST exchange</b><br>
          <br>
          Mariyaiya, please update the FSD with the following confirmed
          decisions from this IST review:<br>
          <br>
          Section 4 (Delete Validations): Add guard — PR cannot be
          deleted or modified once first-level approval is given. Both
          Modify and Delete must be hard-blocked when PRSTATUS is not
          OPEN.<br>
          <br>
          Section 5 (Business Logic): Update the Approval Workflow
          sub-section — SPINRISE implements 2 levels only. L1 =
          Department Heads, L2 = Purchase Officer. No auto-PO generation
          on final approval. PO creation remains a separate manual step.<br>
          <br>
          Section 11 (Customer Variation Register): Update to confirm
          zero customer-specific variations.<br>
          <br>
          Section 12 (SPINRISE Recommendations): Add confirmed design
          decisions — no backdate, 2-level approval, no auto-PO.<br>
          <br>
          For Section 8, the po_para flags for the PR form specifically
          (Manual_IndNo, BudgetQty, PRapprovalstatus, Penpodetails,
          PendingOrderPara, InditemGrp) must be documented with the
          SPINRISE defaults once Muthuvel provides them.<br>
          <br>
          <br>
          <b>Overall status<br>
          </b><br>
          This submission resolves several long-standing open items —
          CustID confirmation, approval architecture, delete/modify
          guard, backdate scope, and partial po_para analysis. The FSD
          is closer to CEO approval than it has ever been.<br>
          <br>
          What remains: IST-3 and IST-4 need improvement from Muthuvel,
          the po_para document needs three corrections, the approval
          workflow form names need to be confirmed, and the OCX
          UserFooter question needs a one-line answer from Palanivel.
          These are all completable today.<br>
          <br>
          PM Saravanan, please coordinate with Muthuvel and Palanivel to
          close the remaining items and submit the consolidated IST
          review — with Palanivel's independent commentary added — for
          CEO review before tomorrow's Saturday meeting.<br>
          <br>
          Regards,<br>
          T. Mani<br>
          <br>
          cc: Mariyaiya (FSD update actions above)</p>
